Ahead of the 2023 general elections, the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) on Tuesday released a revised timetable of activities for its governorship, State House of Assembly, Senate and House of Representatives primary elections. The National Publicity Secretary of the party, Felix Morka made this known in a statement signed and made available to journalists in Abuja. According to the statement, the party’s governorship primaries would now hold on Thursday, 26th of May and the State House of Assembly for Local Government delegates would hold on the same date. -Advertisement- Meanwhile, the Senate primary election would hold on Friday, 27th of May, while the House of Representatives will be on Saturday, 28th of May, 2022. The statement read, “REVISED APC TIMETABLE FOR 2023 PRIMARY ELECTIONS The National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) on Monday, 23rd of May, 2022, approved a revised Timetable/Schedule of Activities for the Governorship, State House of Assembly, Senate and House of Representatives Primary Elections as follows: Thursday, 26th of May, 2022Governorship – (State Delegates)State House of Assembly – (LGA Delegates) Friday, 27th of May, 2022Senate – (LGA Delegates) POLL Saturday, 28th of May, 2022House of Representatives – (LGA Delegates) Please note that the Special Convention for the Presidential Primary will be held as scheduled on Sunday, 29th – Monday, 30th of May, 2022.